As of the [[census]]<ref name="GR2" /> of 2000, there were 1,113 people, 472 households, and 320 families residing in the town. The population density was {{convert|625.5|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. There were 510 housing units at an average density of {{convert|286.6|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of the town was 89.94% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 9.70% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0.09% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 0.09% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], and 0.18% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 0.54% of the population.

[[File:Bradford-bank.jpg|thumb|left|Inside Bradford Bank in 1919.]]

There were 472 households, out of which 25.8% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 53.0% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 12.7% had a female householder with no husband present, and 32.0% were non-families. 27.8% of all households were made up of individuals, and 14.8% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.36 and the average family size was 2.89.

In the town, the population was spread out, with 22.2% under the age of 18, 6.9% from 18 to 24, 25.9% from 25 to 44, 25.6% from 45 to 64, and 19.4% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 41 years. For every 100 females, there were 81.9 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 78.2 males.

The median income for a household in the town was $30,486, and the median income for a family was $36,484. Males had a median income of $31,250 versus $20,250 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the town was $15,609. About 9.1% of families and 14.9% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 29.5% of those under age 18 and 13.6% of those age 65 or over.

